channel.title: Did you know JAVA before starting to make/play private servers?
channel.description:
I know this isn't the correct place, but there isn't any where else to post it while it still being about p'servers.
So the question is, Did you know Java before starting to make private servers?
My self I am just now learning java in the last few weeks. Its currently my 2nd programming language (not including html, php, online coding etc.)
I am betting only a small percentage actually knew it before it.
TBH, most server owners don't know java i have realized. (I didn't know it when i was a server owner lmfao)

item.title: Did you know JAVA before starting to make/play private servers?
item.dc:creator: @Play_N_Skillz Play N Skillz
item.description:
@Play_N_Skillz wrote:

Sighs… Ya, I pretty much just new the basics. Just strings, classes, ints, voids, booleans, and most to the beginner’s knowledge.

I became more experienced at it by a lot of testing. But to do it, I always made a back-up of my client.java, and would just experiment anything I could possibly imagine. Most of my codes didn’t work, but I came around some of the times, and they soon just became accustomed to me. I don’t really spend all that time on my server anymore, but learning more of Java is something I can plan on doing in the future.

Read full topic
